window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The thrilling conclusion of Audible's blockbuster Sherlock Holmes saga brings back Dominic Monaghan and Phil LaMarr in their iconic roles... and introduces the one man who holds the key to Moriarty’s past: Sir Ben Kingsley as Moriarty's father.</b></p> <p>Professor James Moriarty thought he could outwit fate… But when his future-predicting equation falls into the wrong hands, it threatens to ignite a global war. Moriarty is dragged into a deadly race across continents, locked in a twisted duel with Sherlock Holmes himself, and haunted by secrets from his own family that refuse to stay buried.</p> <p>From sinking ships to burning cathedrals, shadow councils to submarine tombs, this season hurtles Moriarty toward a final reckoning where genius, betrayal, and obsession collide.</p> <p><i>Moriarty: The Great Chaos</i> is a globe-spanning thriller that proves the most dangerous equation of all is the one you can’t solve yourself.</p> <p>Available in Dolby Atmos on Audible.</p> <p>Full cast includes: Dominic Monaghan, Phil LaMarr, Joanne Froggatt, Ben Kingsley, Ross McCall, Adam Godley, Billy Harris, Josh Robert Thompson, Nicholas Mongiardo-Cooper, JB Blanc, Lindsay Jean Michelle, Ken Clement, Paul Rogan, Kai Edgar, Dan Domingues, Pranshu Mishra, Sara Matsui-Colby</p>"; 
